Essentially, what do I do if the whole school finds out about everything? Depression, anorexia, cutting, suicide. 
So I was friends with this girl. I was close with her for seven years so I told her about cutting and not eating, but nothing else. Well somehow she found out about everything and got pissed off I didn't tell her in the first place. She told four other kids and they don't talk to me anymore. ~~~~~~ Today we were at a party together. We were laughing about our old drama with some new friends. She told me that her and the kids she told still make fun of me together. They had heard her side of the story, so they asked for my side. I told them what happened, I was unbiased and the mean girl got really pissed off. (Idk why) well now I'm pretty sure the entire grade will know by tomorrow.

This post is in memory of the most loving, caring, compassionate, and tenacious woman I've ever known, my mother. I can't believe it's been two years since you were taken from us. It still all seems so surreal. I love and miss you more than words can describe and honestly I truly just wish you were here. But just know I always bring a part of you with me, and as everyday passes I learn more about myself. I realize I have your flair for fighting for what's right, never backing down and striving to be the best person I can be. I might be struggling at the moment but battles as you've taught me, define who we are, who we want to be and it opens our eyes to what's really important in life. I will continue to fight and not give up because I know that's what you would do. Most of all I will continue to apply what I've learned from you because I am a part of you and I'm damn proud of that. RIP Mom, until we meet again, I love forever and always. Your son, Jason

I just received the award for the number one team at Douglas Elliman, the largest real estate brokerage on the East Coast with almost 5000 agents. It's a big night here at Cipriani for me, my business partner John and our team members. This is not typically an industry where you get recognized like this... You see, I came to New York with nothing really, nothing but a big dream. Never did I expect to climb to the very top in real estate, and never like tonight, to become number one. They say if you are number one in New York, the most competitive real estate environment in the world, then you are number one... well, maybe everywhere. I feel proud because God knows the difficult choices I had to take to get here, my very own way, and all that bloody hard work. As I'm writing this, I also can't help to think of all the naysayers on the way here, and maybe I should dedicate this award to them, wouldn't that be kind of fun?, to those who told me I didn't know the language, that the TV-show would ruin me, that I would never be able to build a company in Scandinavia while being a broker in New York, that I was too young, even that my social media was 'too much' for a broker who deals on this high level. Actually no, the naysayers motivate me and drive me but they don't deserve an award. üòú Instead I'll dedicate this award tonight to my husband, the family back home, friends, team and colleagues at Douglas Elliman. Weeee! And to you here taking the time to read this too long of a text, you who do give me so much support to live right now in that old dream I had when I first arrived to NYC. Oh yes, lastly: New York City... I thank you most of all for letting me run through your veins, BEING you and becoming you, up and down I go within you, your neon, your cobblestoned streets, your history and so so so exciting future, because I do finally understand you now after over 10 years here, and you not only let me sell the hell out of you, I think you always planned this for me. This one goes out to you, New York! ‚ù§Ô∏è

Something about seeing a bunch of beta tapes in a trash truck makes me very sad. There's a whole generation of young editors coming up who won't know that oh so rewarding sound of the deck clicking when you hit record on the digital cut tool. They won't know why Source/Record editing is called Source/Record editing or where the name Insert Edit comes from. True offline editing has changed, and while I embrace that, I miss having one foot in the analog world. You can't hold a QuickTime in your hand. 
#editlife #knowyourhistory

#KALICHALLENGE üí•POWER SNATCHüí•
üí•TAG ANYONE UP FOR THIS CHALLENGEüí•

The power snatch separates the elite competitors vs those riding the bench. The fake assed 'go to the gym to take photos and not workout' posers from those who are really about this life. It primarily develops power and strengthens the 'second pull', or the portion of the lift from above the knee to completion. For those of you with patella issues, it can also be used while limiting lower-body involvement while STILL building strength, power, explosiveness and stabilizing the upper back and external rotators. 
With an open mind, this exercise really is no more difficult to learn than the 'power clean' and teaching by any reasonably competent coach...which is very hard to find nowadays...can provide all the guidance you need to get started in a few training sessions. 
The power snatch is broken down into 6 phases, kinda like connecting the dots, starting with the set-up and the pull. Just replay my vid a few times to help out.

Each phase of the lift must be correct before moving onto the next phase, or your won't 'receive the bar' and your lift WILL FAIL.  Think of each phase of the lift like a picture, and each picture or position needs to be technically correct for maximum power and minimum risk of injury. While some people can lift weights like jack asses, hollering, yelling for attention with bad form and technique, they are not only lifting below their potential, they are increasing their risk of injury. üí•TAG ANYONE WHO'S DOWN TO SNATCHüí•
